result.adr_address: 49 Elgin St, Central, Hong Kong
result.name: Fini's Italian American

reviews.text: Good Italian-inspired food. Not sticking strictly to the traditions but altering classic recipes in very interesting ways. Portions are very healthy so it helps if you are hungry when you come over here (especially if you order the pizzas), as you will get plenty of value for money. The menu is focused without being restrictive so you are very likely find a version of your favourite Italian meal here! Nothing stands out too much though and the service can be rather slow even during relaxed times.

The all you can eat chicken wings and unlimited beer deal here is unbeatable at approx 100 HK dollars per person. Very attentive staff and delicious food made for a memorable experience! Cannot recommend highly enough 👌
I tried happy hours (5 to 7pm). Manager there was super angry for some reason and we felt she were very impolite to people and hope we can have better service for the next time
friendly staff,  good quality food. decent prices

The food is slightly above average generally, but sometimes over-seasoned and the menu isn't too balanced.  Was looking for some greens... but they were out of the broccoli and didn't have a substitute.

result.adr_address: 69 Stone Nullah Ln, Wan Chai, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: 69 Stone Nullah Ln, Wan Chai, Hong Kong
result.name: Fini’s

reviews.text: I dropped in for relaxed latenight beers. An easy ambience with good service. Not a huge space but they seem flexible enough to allow taking drinks outside. Range of beers is not extensive though and they may even be out of stock on some.

LOVED this place. Seriously great food. Great vibe. Really great service - massive shout out to Jenny who gave us exceptional service and made us want to come back a second time - which we did, though sadly Jenny wasn’t on. Huge fan and would come back next time I’m in HK.
Pepperoni pizza is super good and huge! Better come with more than 2 people. Tiramisu as an ending is perfect!

Can't beat the Happy Hour deal - all you can drink beer, fries and Buffalo wings for $108. 

They have another store in Soho with the same deal. 

Grab the seats by the open windows: great vantage point for people watching and be watched.
Great food and service at reasonable price
